      <h3 class="eni-section-title">Indicator Specification</h3>
      <h4>Indicator definition</h4>
      <p>The proposed definition is a combination of the D1 UNECE Environmental Indicator and of the SEBI 007 indicator.  </p>
      <p>The indicator shows the area of terrestrial area protected in compliance with the national legislation and its evolution over time. It reflects both the extent of protected areas and their share in the total area of the country.  </p>

      <p>The indicator can be further broken down by IUCN management categories and by category of national designation (national park, nature reserve, landscape park etc.). In addition, a sub-indicator showing the relation between nationally designated areas at national level and Emerald sites designation can be developed.</p>

      <h4>Units</h4>
      <p>Total area (km2) of nationally designated protected areas as a percentage of the country territory.</p>

      <h3 class="eni-section-title">Rationale</h3>
      <h4>Justification for indicator selection</h4>
      <p>Establishment of protected areas is a direct response to concerns over biodiversity loss, so an indicator in protected area coverage is a valuable indication of commitment to conserving biodiversity and reducing loss at a range of levels.</p>
      <p>The indicator demonstrates the change over time in one form of protection afforded to components of biodiversity. It provides a measure of the response to the degradation of ecosystems and the loss of biodiversity in a country. It demonstrates the extent to which areas important for conserving biodiversity, cultural heritage, scientific research (including baseline monitoring of processes in the ecosystems), recreation, natural resource maintenance and other environmental values are protected.</p>
      <p>National biodiversity strategy and action plan of the Republic of Moldova has defined the expansion of the nationally desginated protected areas as one of the priority areas of work between 2015-2020.</p>

